criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. A new patient coming in for a first office call (FOC) or first consultation via
             telemedicine with a diagnosis of cancer, or

          2. An established patient with a diagnosis of cancer receiving treatment at the AIMS
             Institute;

          3. If over 18 years of age are able to understand study design adequately and provide
             signed informed consent (IC) to enrollment;

          4. If younger than 18 years of age informed assent from the child and informed consent
             from a parent or guardian who is able to understand the study design adequately and
             provide signed informed consent for the pediatric patient;

          5. A confirmed diagnosis of cancer based on medical oncology medical records.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients not diagnosed with cancer;

          2. Telehealth patients;

          3. Cannot read or understand English well enough to read and sign the consent form and
             complete the questionnaires;

          4. Unwilling to participate in the AIMS Institute observational study.
